fields.body:
- switched to Illustrator for best performance, PDF compatibility and reliability on offset technology output options. multi-pages jobs: switched to Indesign  **Results:** more reliable pdf and offset technology output options.

- ganging and imposition process: adopted a software solution instead of manual procedure that often lead to misprints and delays. Software: kodak preps.  **Results:** up to 10 times faster workflow, probability of error reduce by about 70%

- ink flow management: switched from manual to software driven ink flow management with a software called press percent.  **Results:** about 50% less waste of paper and reduction by 60% of machine setting time.

- mock ups: adopted 3d software Software: Google Sketchup  **Results:** new clients,attracted by interactive package mock-ups and faster previews for the clients.
fields.h2_it: miglioramenti del workflow in Digital Grafica:
fields.body_it:
Passaggio ad Illustrator per migliorare le prestazioni, la compatibilità PDF , affidabilità, e migliore gestione dell'output per la tecnologia offset. lavori multi-pagina: migrazione ad Indesign Risultati: migliore gestione dell'output per la tecnologia offset, migliore gestione pagine mastro e documenti ad elevato contenuto testuale.
imposizione e montaggio: adottata una soluzione software alternativa alla procedura manuale (che causava di frequenti ritardi ed errori di stampa). Software: Kodak Preps® Risultati: velocità del flusso di lavoro fino a 10 volte superiore, probabilità di errore ridotte del 70% circa
livello dei calamai su macchine offset: passaggio da gestione manuale a gestione software dei livelli di inchiostrazione tramite files pps generati da un software chiamato presspercent. Risultati: riduzione del 50% circa dello spreco di carta e riduzione del 60% dei tempi di regolazione della macchina
mock up: Utilizzo software 3d Software: Google Sketchup Risultati: Anteprime più veloci, bozze interattive tridimensionali inviabili tramite mail.

fields.body:
My name is Italo Mandara and I'm a Frontend developer (currently working at Artfinder) with a Graphic Design background, Welcome to my portfolio and resume website. This website, was written from scratch using few awesome frameworks such as **Django** (Python backend framework), **Zurb Foundation 6** (Cutting edge responsive framework), and **Jquery** (Famous and very popular Javascript framework). This website is not just my employment channel, it is also my personal playground to do experiments based on new frameworks or just to play with existing *css javascript html* technologies and test new effects.
I strongly recommend using a chrome browser to give a full user experience, but foundation 6 is also compatible with *Firefox, safari* and the latest versions of *Internet explorer* (10 or older recommended ).
fields.body_it: Benvenuti nel mio sito web, questo sito, scritto partendo da zero, è anche uno spazio personale in cui fare esperimenti basati su nuove tecniche o semplicemente per sperimentare tecniche html css javascript esistenti ed ottenere nuovi effetti.

fields.body:
I am a Senior graphic designer and Junior web designer. The areas in which I have experience are advertising, Package Design, Logo Design and Print Publication Design. I have attended courses in Digital Design and have some experience in UI design and Web Design.

I am currently attending online courses for Ux Design. Particularly in my most recent roles I have shown myself to be self-motivated, committed and determined in achieving my goals. I have also demonstrated negotiating, organising and time managing skills and a strong sense of responsibility.

All my jobs required particular attention to technical restraints.
fields.body_it:
Sono un Grafico pubblicitario senior ed un web designer junior. I settori in cui ho esperienza sono: advertising, package design, logo design e pre-stampa. Ho completato recentemente un corso di Digital Design ed ho qualche esperienza in UI/UX design e Web Design. Sto attualmente frequentando corsi di Interaction design.

In particolare nei miei ruoli più recenti ho dimostrato di essere motivato, costante e determinato nel raggiungere i miei obiettivi. ho anche dimostrato capacità di negoziazione, organizzazione, time management ed un grande spirito di responsabilità.

Tutte le mie esperienze lavorative richiedevano attenzione alle restrizioni tecniche.

fields.body: What’s important is the fucking drive to see a project through no matter what. Form follows fucking function. Someday is not a fucking day of the week. Intuition is fucking important. When you design, you have to draw on your own fucking life experiences. If it’s not something you would want to read/look at/use then why fucking bother? To surpass others is fucking tough, if you only do as you are told you don’t have it in you to succeed. Don’t get hung up on things that don’t fucking work. You are not your fucking work. Must-do is a good fucking master. The details are not the details. They make the fucking design. Learn from fucking criticism.

fields.name: visual designer
fields.description: Duties involved creating graphical interface layouts , taking care when required of the Javascript code and visual communication, including advertising posters, business cards, letterheads. I worked in a team, often suggesting and discussing the main guidelines of the project to improve results.
fields.description_it: Il mio incarico consisteva nella creazione di layout dell'interfaccia grafica , avendo cura , se necessario, del codice Javascript e della comunicazione visiva , tra cui manifesti, biglietti da visita , carta intestata e corporate identity. Ho lavorato in una squadra di sviluppatori, talvolta proponendo e discutendo le principali linee guida del progetto per migliorare i risultati .

fields.name: graphic designer
fields.description: I was in charge of creating visual layouts for advertising and web jobs, taking care of the technical pre-press details. In this experience I developed my customer service skills so that the public felt at ease when looking for graphic solutions for their corporate identity. I maintained my calm behavior and positive outlook, even when dealing with nervous customers. I was praised for my professional behavior when I managed "Key Customers" such as banks who preferred to keep in contact with me rather than other employees.
fields.description_it: Ero responsabile della creazione di layout grafici per stampa e web , curando i dettagli tecnici di pre-stampa.  In questa esperienza ho sviluppato le mie capacità di customer care mettendo a proprio agio la clientela mentre proponevo soluzioni grafiche da loro richieste. Ho mantenuto calma e ottimismo, anche in caso di clienti nervosi . Sono stato più volte preso come esempio per il mio comportamento professionale con i " Clienti chiave " come le banche, che hanno preferito di rimanere in contatto con me , piuttosto che con altri dipendenti.

fields.name: graphic designer
fields.description: Duties involved, besides creating advertising layouts, taking care of the technical pre-press details, also meeting with customers and dealing with their enquiries. I completed order forms, provided a draft for the customer to sign in order to confirm the job, and took telephone bookings and orders. In 2010 I was asked to lead the graphics team.
fields.description_it: Le mansioni riguardavano, oltre alla creazione di layout grafici e pre-stampa, anche il coloquio con i clienti, completamento moduli d'ordine, e lavoro di segreteria. Nel 2010 mi è stato chiesto di prendere l'incarico di capo ufficio.

fields.author: Italo Mandara
fields.body: A wonderful serenity has taken possession of my entire soul, like these sweet mornings of spring which I enjoy with my whole heart. I am alone, and feel the charm of existence in this spot, which was created for the bliss of souls like mine. I am so happy, my dear friend, so absorbed in the exquisite sense of mere tranquil existence, that I neglect my talents. I should be incapable of drawing a single stroke at the present moment; and yet I feel that I never was a greater artist than now. When, while the lovely valley teems with vapour around me, and the meridian sun strikes the upper surface of the impenetrable foliage of my trees, and but a few stray gleams steal into the inner sanctuary, I throw myself down among the tall grass by the trickling stream; and, as I lie close to the earth, a thousand unknown plants are noticed by me: when I hear the buzz of the little world among the stalks, and grow familiar with the countless indescribable forms of the insects and flies, then I feel the presence of the Almighty, who formed us in his own image, and the breath

fields.title: Yet another blog post
fields.subtitle: he found himself transformed in his bed into a horrible vermin.
fields.author: Franz Kafka
fields.body: One morning, when Gregor Samsa woke from troubled dreams, he found himself transformed in his bed into a horrible vermin. He lay on his armour-like back, and if he lifted his head a little he could see his brown belly, slightly domed and divided by arches into stiff sections. The bedding was hardly able to cover it and seemed ready to slide off any moment. His many legs, pitifully thin compared with the size of the rest of him, waved about helplessly as he looked. "What's happened to me?" he thought. It wasn't a dream. His room, a proper human room although a little too small, lay peacefully between its four familiar walls. A collection of textile samples lay spread out on the table - Samsa was a travelling salesman - and above it there hung a picture that he had recently cut out of an illustrated magazine and housed in a nice, gilded frame. It showed a lady fitted out with a fur hat and fur boa who sat upright, raising a heavy fur muff that covered the whole of her lower arm towards the viewer. Gregor then turned to look out the window at the dull weather. Drops
